{"id":"history-of-computer-science","files":[{"path":"ATTRIBUTION.md","encoding":"utf8","data":"# Image and research attribution\n\nTwo women operating ENIAC, U.S. Army photograph/public domain via Wikimedia Commons\nSpecial:FilePath.\n\nEach lesson uses a distinct remote image and includes a research source link in its notes. The\nremote images are not redistributed in this source package; the reader displays them when connected\nand preserves the local SVG cover offline. Verify current reuse details at each linked Wikimedia\nCommons file page before commercial redistribution.\n\n- **Algorithms Before Computers** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Al-Khwarizmi.jpg; research source:\n  https://computerhistory.org/blog/the-neverending-quest-for-firsts/\n- **Ada Lovelace and General Purpose Ideas** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Ada_Lovelace_portrait.jpg; research source:\n  https://computerhistory.org/minecraft/non-player-characters/\n- **The Electronic Era** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Two_women_operating_ENIAC.gif; research\n  source: https://womenshistory.si.edu/human-computer-project\n- **Programming Languages** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Grace_Hopper_and_UNIVAC.jpg; research source:\n  https://computerhistory.org/timeline/software/\n- **Networks Change Scale** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Internet_map_1024.jpg; research source:\n  https://www.computerhistory.org/internethistory/\n- **Computing and Responsibility** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Portrait_of_Grace_Hopper.jpg; research source:\n  https://www.americanhistory.si.edu/explore/stories/just-planning-dinner-feminization-computer-programming\n"},{"path":"assets/images/cover.svg","encoding":"utf8","data":"<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\"><rect w